nd if not for one single MoS warrior named Gabriell and one druid named Bridgit I would not have the gear that I have now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I digress...  What is boils down to is that there is not a single person in this game that is not in some fashion,at some time somewhat selfish.  The thing that everyone has to remember is to be generous when it counts, with your guild.  Give time, advice, help, anything that you can when you can.  That's all anyone can ask of you IMO.  I know where I would stand if a &quot;Light Uber Defender's War Sword of Dragon Toenail Clipping&quot; dropped and was ranger usable.  The difference is that if I lost a roll to a guildie I would not feel near as bad.<br>
<br>
